      "message": "\u003e Nice.  I was just toying around with ways to make this little section of code faster.  I notice it\u0027s the profile hot spot when I load up \"The Machine\".json.\n\nYup, I expect short strings to be hot for Skottie as the vast majority of Lottie strings are 1-2 chars.\n\n\n\u003e Ideas:\n\u003e    1) can we know when it\u0027s safe to load 8 bytes and mask in a \\0, or when we need to carefully memcpy exactly size bytes?\n\u003e    2) can we avoid storing len_tag for short strings?\n\n#2 may be an obvious win: at least for now, nobody cares about string lengths.  And if that happens in the future, strlen should be okish for short strings.",
